results.brief_description: Magazine items: Heron sailing, Canberra. A poetic glimpse of Heron class yachts on Lake Burley Griffin; Pre-school kindergarten. results.title: Australian diary. No. 132
results.brief_description: Magazine items: Drought, A sheep station in N.S.W. faces ruin because of one of the worst-ever droughts; rain has not fallen for 18 months and water for limited use is brought in by truck. Bundaberg: the Queensland coastal port which serves a rich agricultural area with a near tropical climate and rich volcanic soil. Birth place of the famous airman, Bert Hinkler, it is a prosperous city which thrives on the extensive sugar cane industry. No other credits available.

results.title: Australian diary. No. 131
results.brief_description: Magazine items: Mobile classroom N.S.W. results.brief_description: Magazine items: Crop protection from the air. Use of aircraft for pasture improvement and pest control has been developed to a high state of efficiency, through the combined efforts of the farmer and the flier. Coal mines close but the people of Cessnock, N.S.W. work an “industrial miracle”.

University College of Townsville is the first in the state of Queensland outside Brisbane.
